Looking at the skill context, it says these should exist:
```csharp
Assert.Contains("expected", actualString);
Assert.StartsWith("prefix", actualString);
Assert.EndsWith("suffix", actualString);
Assert.MatchesRegex(@"\d{3}-\d{4}", phoneNumber);


```

But the installed version (3.8.2) doesn't have them. These might be MSTest 4.x APIs. Let me check what's available on NuGet to see if I need to upgrade or use `StringAssert` instead.

